  "text": "[10] The SiBCASA fire emissions (CO 2 and 13 CO 2 ) follow the methodology of van der [CITATION_1] . The estimated fire emissions are driven by multiple remotely sensed burned area products combined in the Global Fire Emissions Database (GFED) version 3.1 . Only above ground, fine litter pools and coarse woody debris at the surface were subject to combustion. Peat burning [CITATION_2] and organic soil carbon combustion were not taken into account for this publication. The global averaged biomass burning flux for the period 1991-2007 amounts to 1.82˙0.17 PgC yr -1 , which is similar to the value of 2.0 PgC yr -1 published by van der Werf et al. [2010] .",
